Now I need to look at the proof toggle code more carefully. I can see from `plastex.js`:Lines 66-84 handle the proof toggle:

```javascript
$("div.proof_heading").click(
  function() {
    var proofWrapper = $(this).closest('.proof_wrapper');
    var sbsContainer = $(this).closest('.sbs-container');

    // Toggle expanded state (CSS handles chevron rotation)
    if (proofWrapper.hasClass('expanded')) {
      proofWrapper.removeClass('expanded');
      // Also hide the Lean proof body
      sbsContainer.find('.lean-proof-body').slideUp();
    } else {
      proofWrapper.addClass('expanded');
      // Also show the Lean proof body
      sbsContainer.find('.lean-proof-body').slideDown(300, function() {
          $(this).css('display', 'inline');
      });
    };
    $(this).siblings("div.proof_content").slideToggle()
  })
```

So when you click the proof heading:
1. It toggles the `expanded` class on `.proof_wrapper`
2. It slides up/down the `.lean-proof-body` within the `.sbs-container`
3. It slides the `.proof_content` 

The user is saying that when this happens, "all of the lean code jumps around its box". This sounds like there's a layout reflow happening during the animation.The issue is likely in how the Lean code is being animated. Let me look at the CSS for `.lean-proof-body` to see if there are any animations or transitions defined.

Looking at the CSS, I don't see explicit styles for `.lean-proof-body` in blueprint.css. Let me check common.css which is mentioned as a dependency.

Perfect! Now I can see the HTML structure. Looking at lines 138-164, I can see how the Lean column is rendered:```lean
def renderLeanColumn (data : SbsData) : String :=
  let codeContent := match data.signatureHtml, data.proofBodyHtml with
    | some sig, some proof =>      s!"<code class=\"hl lean lean-signature\">{sig}</code><code class=\"hl lean lean-proof-body\">{proof}</code>"
    | some sig, none =>
      s!"<code class=\"hl lean lean-signature\">{sig}</code>"
    | none, some proof =>
      s!"<code class=\"hl lean lean-proof-body\">{proof}</code>"
    | none, none =>
      ...  s!"<div class=\"sbs-lean-column\">
  <pre class=\"lean-code hl lean\"{hoverAttr}>
{codeContent}
  </pre>
</div>"```

So the structure is:```html
<div class="sbs-lean-column">
  <pre class="lean-code hl lean">
    <code class="hl lean lean-signature">...</code>
    <code class="hl lean lean-proof-body">...</code>
  </pre>
</div>
```

Now, looking back at the JavaScript in plastex.js (lines 75-82):```javascript
if (proofWrapper.hasClass('expanded')) {
  proofWrapper.removeClass('expanded');
  // Also hide the Lean proof body
  sbsContainer.find('.lean-proof-body').slideUp();
} else {
  proofWrapper.addClass('expanded');
  // Also show the Lean proof body
  sbsContainer.find('.lean-proof-body').slideDown(300, function() {
      $(this).css('display', 'inline');
  });
};


```

I see the issue now. The `.lean-proof-body` is a `<code>` element nested inside `<pre>`, and when `slideDown()` animates it, jQuery temporarily sets `overflow: hidden` and manipulates the height. Once the animation finishes, the callback forces `display: inline`, which causes a jarring reflow since `<code>` elements should naturally be inline. The transition from block-level display during animation to inline after creates the visual glitch.

The `.lean-signature` element also shifts because the parent container's height changes during the animation. I should either use `fadeIn()`/`fadeOut()` to avoid height manipulation, wrap the code element in a container div that can handle the slide animation, or switch to CSS transitions with `max-height` instead.
```

Aha! So before commit 2063d35, the code was using `slideUp()` and `slideDown()` without any callback! That's the version that was working.The problematic callback `.css('display', 'inline')` was added in commit 2063d35 to "fix: resolve one-line gap in proof toggle animation (#175)".

So the working version was:
```javascript
if (proofWrapper.hasClass('expanded')) {
  proofWrapper.removeClass('expanded');
  sbsContainer.find('.lean-proof-body').slideUp();
} else {
  proofWrapper.addClass('expanded');
